swPimSmMIB.name: swPimSmMIB
swPimSmMIB.description: The Structure of PIM SM Information for the proprietary enterprise.

swPimRegisterProbeTime.name: swPimRegisterProbeTime
swPimRegisterProbeTime.description: Used to set a time to send a probe message from the Designated Router (DR) to the Rendezvous Point (RP) before the Register Suppression time expires. If a Register Stop message is received by the DR, the Register Suppression Time will be restarted. If no Register Stop message is received within the probe time, Register Packets will be resent to the RP. The default value is 5 seconds.

swPimRegisterSuppressionTime.name: swPimRegisterSuppressionTime
swPimRegisterSuppressionTime.description: The time interval between receiving a Register-Stop message and restarting the process of sending of register messages again. A lower value represents an increase in register messages being sent to the RP, while a higher value represents a longer latency period for new receivers wishing to join the group.

swPimInfoTable.name: swPimInfoTable
swPimInfoTable.description: The PIM Information Table contains PIM related information, such as DR priority.

swPimInfoEntry.name: swPimInfoEntry
swPimInfoEntry.description: An entry in the PIM Information Table.

swPimInfoInterface.name: swPimInfoInterface
swPimInfoInterface.description: The ifIndex value of this PIM interface.

swPimInfoAddress.name: swPimInfoAddress
swPimInfoAddress.description: The IP address of the PIM interface.

swPimInfoNetMask.name: swPimInfoNetMask
swPimInfoNetMask.description: The network mask for the IP address of the PIM interface.

swPimInfoDesignatedRouter.name: swPimInfoDesignatedRouter
swPimInfoDesignatedRouter.description: The Designated Router on this PIM interface. For point-to- point interfaces, this object has the value 0.0.0.0.

swPimInfoHelloInterval.name: swPimInfoHelloInterval
swPimInfoHelloInterval.description: The frequency at which PIM Hello messages are transmitted on this interface.

swPimInfoJoinPruneInterval.name: swPimInfoJoinPruneInterval
swPimInfoJoinPruneInterval.description: The frequency at which PIM Join/Prune messages are transmitted on this PIM interface. The default value of this object is the pimJoinPruneInterval.

swPimInfoDRPriority.name: swPimInfoDRPriority
swPimInfoDRPriority.description: The DR Priority sets the priority of an IP interface to become the Designated router for the multiple access network. A numerically larger priority is always preferred, yet a lower number represents a higher priority. A router's knowledge of the current DR on an interface can change when a PIM Hello message is received, when a neighbor timers out, or when a router's own DR priority changes.

swPimInfoMode.name: swPimInfoMode
swPimInfoMode.description: The configured mode of this PIM interface. A value of sparseDense is only valid for PIMv1.

swPimInfoState.name: swPimInfoState
swPimInfoState.description: The configured state of this PIM interface.

swpimCbsrBootStrapPeriod.name: swpimCbsrBootStrapPeriod
swpimCbsrBootStrapPeriod.description: The time interval, in seconds, for Boot Strap Messages originating from the elected BSR.

swPimCbsrHashMaskLen.name: swPimCbsrHashMaskLen
swPimCbsrHashMaskLen.description: The length (in bits) of the mask to use for the hash function(This hash algorithm will be used to determine which candidate RP will be the RP for the PIM-SM network.).For IPv4 we recommend a value of 30. For IPv6 we recommand a value of 126.

swPimCbsrTable.name: swPimCbsrTable
swPimCbsrTable.description: The PIM CBSR Table contains the candidate bootstrap router related information, such as interface name, IP address and priority.

swPimCbsrEntry.name: swPimCbsrEntry
swPimCbsrEntry.description: An entry in the PIM CBSR Table.

swPimCbsrInterface.name: swPimCbsrInterface
swPimCbsrInterface.description: The ifIndex value of this PIM interface.

swPimCbsrIpAddress.name: swPimCbsrIpAddress
swPimCbsrIpAddress.description: The IP address of this PIM interface.

swPimCbsrSubnetMask.name: swPimCbsrSubnetMask
swPimCbsrSubnetMask.description: The IP netmask for this PIM interface.

swPimCbsrPriority.name: swPimCbsrPriority
swPimCbsrPriority.description: The preference value for the local candidate interface to become a bootstrap router. The value of -1 is used to indicate the local candidate interface cannot become the BSR.

swPimCandidateRPHoldtime.name: swPimCandidateRPHoldtime
swPimCandidateRPHoldtime.description: Used to set the time CRP advertisements remain valid on the PIM-SM enabled network. If these advertisements, set here, aren't received by the BSR within this time period, the CRP will be removed from the list of candidates. 0 states to the BSR that this CRP should immediately be removed. Default: 150 seconds.

swPimCandidateRPPriority.name: swPimCandidateRPPriority
swPimCandidateRPPriority.description: This value determines the priority of a CRP to become the RP for the distribution tree. A lower value denotes a higher priority. If there is a tie for priority, the device with the highest IP address will become the RP. This information is stored in the BSR, along with the RP address and corresponding encoded group address.

swPimCandidateRPWildcardPrefixCnt.name: swPimCandidateRPWildcardPrefixCnt
swPimCandidateRPWildcardPrefixCnt.description: The number of enocded group addresses included in the message; indicating the group prefixes for which the C-RP is advertising. A Prefix-Cnt of '0' implies a prefix of 224.0.0.0 with mask length of 4; i.e. all multicast groups. If the C-RP is not configured with Group-prefix information, the C-RP puts a default value of '0' in this field.

swPimCandidateRPTable.name: swPimCandidateRPTable
swPimCandidateRPTable.description: The (conceptual) table listing the IP multicast groups for which the local router is to advertise itself as a Candidate-RP when the value of pimComponentCRPHoldTime is non-zero. If this table is empty, then the local router will advertise itself as a Candidate-RP for all groups (providing the value of pimComponentCRPHoldTime is non- zero).

swPimCandidateRPEntry.name: swPimCandidateRPEntry
swPimCandidateRPEntry.description: An entry (conceptual row) in the pimCandidateRPTable.

swPimCandidateRPGroupAddress.name: swPimCandidateRPGroupAddress
swPimCandidateRPGroupAddress.description: The IP multicast group address which, when combined with pimCandidateRPGroupMask, identifies a group prefix for which the local router will advertise itself as a Candidate-RP.

swPimCandidateRPGroupMask.name: swPimCandidateRPGroupMask
swPimCandidateRPGroupMask.description: The multicast group address mask which, when combined with pimCandidateRPGroupMask, identifies a group prefix for which the local router will advertise itself as a Candidate-RP.

swPimCandidateRPInterface.name: swPimCandidateRPInterface
swPimCandidateRPInterface.description: The name of the interface which will be advertised as a Candidate-RP.

swPimCandidateRPRowStatus.name: swPimCandidateRPRowStatus
swPimCandidateRPRowStatus.description: The status of this row, by which new entries may be created, or old entries deleted from this table.

swPimNeighborTable.name: swPimNeighborTable
swPimNeighborTable.description: The (conceptual) table listing the router's PIM neighbors.

swPimNeighborEntry.name: swPimNeighborEntry
swPimNeighborEntry.description: An entry (conceptual row) in the swPimNeighborTable.

swPimNeighborAddress.name: swPimNeighborAddress
swPimNeighborAddress.description: The IP address of the PIM neighbor for which to find PIM neighbor information.

swPimNeighborIfIndex.name: swPimNeighborIfIndex
swPimNeighborIfIndex.description: The value of ifIndex for the interface used for which to find PIM neighbor information.

swPimNeighborExpiryTime.name: swPimNeighborExpiryTime
swPimNeighborExpiryTime.description: The minimum time remaining before this PIM neighbor ages out.

swPimLastHopSptSwitchover.name: swPimLastHopSptSwitchover
swPimLastHopSptSwitchover.description: Used by the last hop router to decide whether to receive the multicast data from the shared tree or switch over to the shortest path tree. When the switchover mode is set to be never, the last hop router will always receive the multicast data from the shared tree. When the mode is set to immediately, the last hop router will always receive the multicast data from the shortest path tree.

swPimRegChksumIncDataTable.name: swPimRegChksumIncDataTable
swPimRegChksumIncDataTable.description: The PIM Register Checksum Including Data Table contains the PIM register checksum including data information, such as RP address and state.

swPimRegChksumIncDataEntry.name: swPimRegChksumIncDataEntry
swPimRegChksumIncDataEntry.description: An entry in the PIM Register Checksum Including Data Table.

swL3SwPimRegChksumIncDataState.name: swL3SwPimRegChksumIncDataState
swL3SwPimRegChksumIncDataState.description: The state of register checksum including data for RPs.

swPimStaticRPTable.name: swPimStaticRPTable
swPimStaticRPTable.description: The PIM Static RP Table contains the PIM static RP related information, such as group address, group mask, RP address and RP row status.

swPimStaticRPEntry.name: swPimStaticRPEntry
swPimStaticRPEntry.description: An entry in the PIM Static RP Table.

swPimStaticRPGroupAddress.name: swPimStaticRPGroupAddress
swPimStaticRPGroupAddress.description: The IP multicast group address which, when combined with swPimStaticRPGroupMask, identifies a group prefix for which the local router will advertise itself as a static RP.

swPimStaticRPGroupMask.name: swPimStaticRPGroupMask
swPimStaticRPGroupMask.description: The multicast group address mask which, when combined with swPimStaticRPGroupAddress, identifies a group prefix for which the local router will advertise itself as a static RP.

swPimStaticRPAddress.name: swPimStaticRPAddress
swPimStaticRPAddress.description: The (unicast) address of the interface which will be advertised as a static RP.

swPimStaticRPRowStatus.name: swPimStaticRPRowStatus
swPimStaticRPRowStatus.description: The status of this row, by which new entries may be created, or old entries deleted from this table.

swPimIpMRouteTable.name: swPimIpMRouteTable
swPimIpMRouteTable.description: The (conceptual) table listing PIM-specific information on a subset of the rows of the ipMRouteTable defined in the IP Multicast MIB.

swPimIpMRouteEntry.name: swPimIpMRouteEntry
swPimIpMRouteEntry.description: An entry (conceptual row) in the pimIpMRouteTable. There is one entry, per entry in the ipMRouteTable, whose incoming interface is running PIM.

swPimIpMRouteGroup.name: swPimIpMRouteGroup
swPimIpMRouteGroup.description: The IP multicast group address for which this entry contains multicast routing information.

swPimIpMRouteSource.name: swPimIpMRouteSource
swPimIpMRouteSource.description: The network address which, when combined with the corresponding value of ipMRouteSourceMask, identifies the sources for which this entry contains multicast routing information.

swPimIpMRouteSourceMask.name: swPimIpMRouteSourceMask
swPimIpMRouteSourceMask.description: The network mask which, when combined with the corresponding value of ipMRouteSource, identifies the sources for which this entry contains multicast routing information.

swPimIpMRouteUpstreamAssertTimer.name: swPimIpMRouteUpstreamAssertTimer
swPimIpMRouteUpstreamAssertTimer.description: The time remaining before the router changes its upstream neighbor back to its RPF neighbor. This timer is called the Assert timer in the PIM Sparse and Dense mode specification. A value of 0 indicates that no Assert timer has changed the upstream neighbor away from the RPF neighbor.

swPimIpMRouteAssertMetric.name: swPimIpMRouteAssertMetric
swPimIpMRouteAssertMetric.description: The metric advertised by the assert winner on the upstream interface, or 0 if no such assert is received.

swPimIpMRouteAssertMetricPref.name: swPimIpMRouteAssertMetricPref
swPimIpMRouteAssertMetricPref.description: The preference advertised by the assert winner on the upstream interface, or 0 if no such assert is in effect.

swPimIpMRouteAssertRPTBit.name: swPimIpMRouteAssertRPTBit
swPimIpMRouteAssertRPTBit.description: The value of the RPT-bit advertised by the assert winner on the upstream interface, or false if no such assert is in effect.

swPimIpMRouteFlags.name: swPimIpMRouteFlags
swPimIpMRouteFlags.description: This object describes PIM-specific flags related to a multicast state entry. See the PIM Sparse Mode specification for the meaning of the RPT and SPT bits.

swPimIpMRouteType.name: swPimIpMRouteType
swPimIpMRouteType.description: This object describes the PIM-specific type as related to a multicast state entry.

swPimRPSetTable.name: swPimRPSetTable
swPimRPSetTable.description: The (conceptual) table listing PIM information for candidate Rendezvous Points (CRPs) for IP multicast groups. When the local router is the BSR, this information is obtained from received Candidate-RP-Advertisements. When the local router is not the BSR, this information is obtained from received RP-Set messages.

swPimRPSetEntry.name: swPimRPSetEntry
swPimRPSetEntry.description: An entry (conceptual row) in the pimRPSetTable.

swPimRPSetComponent.name: swPimRPSetComponent
swPimRPSetComponent.description: A number uniquely identifying the component. Each protocol instance connected to a separate domain should have a different index value.

swPimRPSetGroupAddress.name: swPimRPSetGroupAddress
swPimRPSetGroupAddress.description: The IP multicast group address which, when combined with pimRPSetGroupMask, gives the group a prefix. This prefix will determine for which entry CRP information is to be displayed, and which entry contains information about the Candidate-RP.

swPimRPSetGroupMask.name: swPimRPSetGroupMask
swPimRPSetGroupMask.description: The multicast group address mask which, when combined with pimRPSetGroupAddress, gives the group a prefix to determine and which entry contains which entry CRP information is to be displayed for which this entry contains information about the Candidate-RP.

swPimRPSetAddress.name: swPimRPSetAddress
swPimRPSetAddress.description: The IP address of the Candidate-RP.
